name: Kedai MakMoon
address: depan mami in home stay, Sumberkima, Kec. Gerokgak, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81155, Indonesia
review 1: It's unbelievable to stumble across such exquisite and creative food skills on a small dusty roadside between Lovina and Singaraja. The food, of international restaurant standard, is expertly and lovingly prepared by the lady out back with very simple equipment. Kedai Makmoon is also distinguished by the modern cleanliness of their otherwise authentic warung status. Sensational and extremely affordable go-to dishes include spicy nasi goreng, dim sum wantons, deep fried stuffed noodle balls and a Balinese take on pad Thai. All of these washed down with icy fresh fruit juices is precisely what every traveller needs for the long drive out to Gili Putih.
